Afterward, the temperature of MAPbI3 layer would increase, and the thermal conduction between MAPbI3 and PDMS results in the temperature rise of PDMS. At last, the PDMS layer is thermally expanded and contracted, following the light pulse, producing ultrasound waves. The generated acoustic pressure is expressed by the following equation28:1P0=νβΔT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
